Loved the food!! We ordered Tallarin Saltado con Camarones, Arroz con Mariscos & the Peruvian Combo for a group of five and it was filling. The Peruvian Combo consists of the chicken, French fries and salad (hence it’s name). The Tallarin Saltado con Camarones uses a Chinese lo mein like noodle that suits my taste much more than the typical type of linguini pasta with its texture being more smooth and slurpy. Overall, all the dishes we ordered were delicious and better than I had originally expected. Would recommend and likely re-visit the place if not its other locations! This location is also basically right next to the train station exit so easy to get to.

Love Pio Pio chicken and the green sauce, but this location is lacking in food quality, customer service and organization compared to it's Manhattan location. There were several times where the chicken was dry as if it had been out for a while. Be sure to ask for the name of whoever is taking your reservation over the phone, because they are disorganized on that end and there is a high chance they will lose it. Service can be a hit or miss, especially when it is not busy.

Two words. Must Visit! Whenever, I'm in town from the Midwest, this place is my must-stop place. Their Madator Combo and Jalea Platter are to dream for. I can't explain the seasonings used for the chicken, but it's earth moving. The skin itself is crispy and lip-smacking good. The seafood in the platter is plentiful and so fresh. Each entree is filled with enough food that you will be taking some home. This place is an A+. An destination spot while in BK.
